<br>
Simply put, gamers really don't care (thus the amazing 'restraint' we've seen) enough about this &quot;issue&quot; to get so worked up about it that they delete their character and leave the server. Can anyone really imagine a High level &quot;uber&quot; member of this community posting &quot;d3wd, y0u RP n4zi's s0xx0r, y0u l4m3rs WIN! I'm g0n3!&quot; ? Most don't speak like this hehe... my point is immerrsion can be ruined, power gaming cannot be ruined.<br>
<br>
In the end no matter what your stance is on the Gameplay styles of this server, if your ultimate goal is the server remaining a place you'd like to play, your better off keeping the peace and not bickering. That is unless your goal is to drive roleplayers off.<br>
<br>
As for Shintou, maybe he'll simply delete Shintou and start fresh, perhaps not reading the boards this time through. I'd suggest that over him leaving altogether.<br>
