<br>
I think the Moderators dropped the ball on enforcing the rules they themselves wrote.  The first rule of this server is &quot;No personal attacks or harrassment of any kind towards any player.&quot;<br>
<br>
For at least two weeks, Shintou was bombarded with every sort of name-callling I can imagine, mostly from the same three posters.  He was a &quot;whiner&quot;, he was a &quot;fanatic&quot;, he was an &quot;extremist&quot;, he was a &quot;racist&quot;, he was a &quot;nazi&quot;, he was any-name-you-could-throw-at-him-that-would-discredit-what-he-was-saying.  These posters were not attacking the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>content</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> of his posts, but the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>person</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> making the argument.  And these posters were relentless in their repitition of these <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    ad hominem</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> attacks.<br>
<br>
None of the Moderators did or said anything about that name-calling.<br>
<br>
And then I see that one of the Moderators joined in the attack.<br>
<br>
Well, no wonder the rules weren't enforced on those attacking Shintou (not Shintou's ideas).<br>
<br>
It's one thing for the Moderators to express their opinions.  That's fine with me.  It's another thing for the Moderators to expressly violate the rules they've set up for the board in the expression of their opinion.<br>
<br>
