<br>
I noticed moderators on this board participating &quot;actively&quot; on threads along time ago. I even brought it up to Valquiss. But I wasn't confrontational about it. It was just a discussion. Basically, my thoughts are this...<br>
<br>
First, while this board is a public board, it is still owned by somebody and that somebody makes the rules. Jaxy I believe is the owner and she and her Moderators help with the rules being created, enforced and revised.<br>
<br>
Second, its true that &quot;Moderator&quot; does imply nuetrality, but thats all it does. The title moderator is just a label and the owner(s) of this board can chose to define &quot;Moderator&quot; any way they see fit. Hell, half the Moderators my country's Government selects are the farthest fooking thing from nuetral and their actions show it (but I'm not bitter).<br>
<br>
I know other moderators on other boards that have 2 accounts. One for posting, another for moderating. That way they can express their opinions and keep their moderator name out of it. Does this seem wrong? Maybe. But they sure don't get half the flack the moderators get on this board.<br>
<br>
The moderators on this board have chosen not too hide behind another account and have decided to express their opinions on some threads without restraint. There's nothing wrong with that. This is fine as long as they follow the same rules we are expected to follow while they post.<br>
<br>
Ankles posted her thoughts and opinions regarding Shintou. She wrote, &quot;You are ruining the boards you have whined so hard to protect.&quot;. I don't see this as a personal attack. I see this as a very blunt statement to get a poster to change their tone. Perhaps this could have been done privately, but then again maybe it needed to be done publicly; to drive the point home that the type of language and tones used by that poster were not acceptable.<br>
<br>
The moderators on this board are intelligent, articulate, funny and they happen to have opinions too. I don't see them as nuetral parties &quot;referee'ing&quot; this board. I gave that vision up long ago over the TLC stuff. I do see them as active participants on this board that also have the ability to enforce the rules we are all expected to follow. I think if everyone just steps back and can re-think how they define &quot;moderator&quot;, that is, let go of the concept of nuetrality, then they will be able to appreciate some of the posts these folks have done and quite possibly engage in some great discussion.<br>
